\subsection{Geometry type of a Belyi map}
\begin{definition}\label{belyi.geometry_type}
\uses{belyi.galmap,group.triangle_group}
A {{KNOWL('belyi.galmap', 'Belyi map')}} corresponds to a finite index subgroup of a {{KNOWL('group.triangle_group', 'triangle group')}} $\Delta(a,b,c)$. The **geometry type** of a Belyi map is spherical, Euclidean, or hyperbolic according to $\frac{1}{a}+\frac{1}{b}+\frac{1}{c}$ being $>1$, $=1$, or $<1$, respectively.
\end{definition}


